{"id": 2694, "date": "2018-06-21T04:33:23", "date_gmt": "2018-06-21T11:33:23", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=2694"}, "modified": "2020-11-30T06:58:03", "modified_gmt": "2020-11-30T14:58:03", "slug": "cover-me-you-cant-sit-down", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2018/06/21/cover-me-you-cant-sit-down/", "title": {"rendered": "Cover Me: You Can&#8217;t Sit Down"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>Whenever Bruce visits Philly, odds are pretty good that he&#8217;ll break out &#8220;You Can&#8217;t Sit Down&#8221; in the encores.</p>\n<p>Made famous by local group The Dovells, this encore cover favorite goes back a ways farther. It was originally released as an instrumental in 1959 by The Bim Bam Boos. Take a listen to that first incarnation&#8211;it&#8217;s certainly recognizable, but it swings more than rocks:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/_8Cg_uCe1to?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>That&#8217;s a young Philip Upchurch on guitar. Two years later, he recorded and released it on his own, changing the title a bit to &#8220;You Can&#8217;t Sit Down.&#8221; Still an instrumental, it&#8217;s a lot more rocking, and you can hear the signature handclaps:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/rKZ1q75vBEo?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Fast forward another two years, add lyrics, and we&#8217;ve got the version that made it to #3 on the Billboard pop chart. It&#8217;s probably that this was the first version to capture Bruce&#8217;s attention, but both the Upchurch and Dovell versions feature a rocking beat and smoking sax solo that were bound to capture Bruce&#8217;s imagination.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/a_UMfzQfJB8?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Bruce has performed &#8220;You Can&#8217;t Sit Down&#8221; so many times in concert that it&#8217;s difficult to find one standout performance. But this one has to be a contender&#8211;from Bruce&#8217;s Darkness show in Houston:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/FYxRoKxneh8?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>You Can&#8217;t Sit Down<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> August 1, 1976 (Red Bank, NJ)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> September 2, 2012 (Philadelphia, PA)</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>&#8220;You Can&#8217;t Sit Down&#8221; is a Philly favorite, made famous by local boys The Dovells. But its origins trace back farther.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 2832, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_mi_skip_tracking": false, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false, "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_is_tweetstorm": false, "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "enabled": false}}}, "categories": [4], "tags": [1215, 508, 435, 1214, 1213, 905], "jetpack_publicize_connections": [], "aioseo_notices": [], "jetpack_featured_media_url": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/dovells-youca-e1529348422263.png?fit=500%2C500&ssl=1", "jetpack_sharing_enabled": true, "jetpack_shortlink": "https://wp.me/p9w3Lk-Hs", "jetpack_likes_enabled": true, "jetpack-related-posts": [{"id": 1749, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2018/04/28/where-the-band-was-philadelphia-april-28-2009/", "url_meta": {"origin": 2694, "position": 0}, "title": "Where the Band Was: Philadelphia, April 28, 2009", "date": "April 28, 2018", "format": false, "excerpt": "On Night One (of six!) in Philadelphia on the Working on a Dream tour, Bruce granted my all-time most-wished-for chase song.", "rel": "", "context": "In &quot;Where the Band Was&quot;", "img": {"alt_text": "", "src": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/20090428_front.jpg?fit=570%2C570&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200", "width": 350, "height": 200}, "classes": []}, {"id": 41825, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2023/02/20/kingdom-of-days-february-20-2/", "url_meta": {"origin": 2694, "position": 1}, "title": "Kingdom of Days: February 20", 